folder: West Street & Bank Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
West Street, Bank Street, to Bethune Street. (Before Reconstruction).
President Borough of Manhatten.
June 9, 1918.

folder: West Street & Bank Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
West Street, south from Bank Street, opposite Pier 49, North River, showing the West Side Elevated Highway under construction. This is the first link to be built, and runs from 23rd Street to just north of Canal Street. See the view at Spring Street, October 27 of this year.

Summer 1930.

Ewing Galloway.

folder: Bank Street & West Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Bank Street, north side, east from West Street.

April 18, 1931,

P.L. Sperr.

Bank Street, east from West Street, showing the W.P.A. resurfacing this street. On Washington and Greenwich Streets respectively, appear the raised road beds of the New York Central Railroad and the Ninth Ave. Elevated Line. August 12, 1936. W.P.A. Photo. Federal Art Project.
